    "Still, the bigger question is, can we classify cryptocurrencies into taxonomies and forecast individual Altcoin categories' future success or failure?",
    "Another important topic discussed in this article is related to cryptocurrencies, the idea of Central Bank Digital Currencies (CBDCs) (Reserve and \"Central Bank Digital Currency (CBDC)\", 2022; Hansen and Delak 2022; Cheng 2022), and Friedrich von Hayekʼs theory of private money, which some experts argue could lead to national currencies being replaced by 'the currency of the digital platform' (Mikhaylov 2021).",
    "Another point on centralisation is that even cryptocurrencies that are meant to be very decentralised, such as Ethereum (ETH), and stablecoins, such as UDSC, can be (in reality) very centralised and potentially controllable.",
